    • start

      public UUID start(IWinApplication appID, CoreStartOptions options)
      Starts an application with whether by using its path or its windowsID some variables and packages are installed while starting the WinApp Driver for the first time as following:

      download and install nodejs from ... add to Path---> C:\Program Files\nodejs run --> npm i appium-windows-driver (to install node-modules , if it not existing in resources) add APPIUM_BINARY_PATH --> C:\core\node_modules\appium\build\lib\main.js run --> npm install -g appium@next add to path %appdata%/npm run ---> appium driver install windows

      Parameters:
      appID - application id/path
      options - CoreStartOptions could contains different ip
      Returns:
      UUID of the created windowsDriver
